timelineItems.text: GOAL - Cyle Larin gets the equalizer in the 17' 1-1 and the @CitrusBowl is rocking #ORLvCLB

timelineItems.text: GOOAAALLLL!! GET IN!!!! #ORLvCLB http://t.co/N98fzfquXi

timelineItems.desc: Orlando City SC and Columbus Crew SC meet for a third time this season in a vital match for both clubs’ ambitions when they face off Saturday evening at the Citrus Bowl.
timelineItems.title: KICKOFF: Orlando City SC vs Columbus Crew SC | August 1, 2015

timelineItems.desc: Attempt saved. Cyle Larin (Orlando City SC) right footed shot from the center of the box is saved in the bottom left corner.
timelineItems.title: SHOT: Cyle Larin denied by Steve Clark early on

timelineItems.name: Adam Jardy
timelineItems.text: Corey Ashe got behind Chad Barson along the left flank, then fed a cross through the heart of the #CrewSC defense to Larin, who buried it.

timelineItems.name: Orlando City SC
timelineItems.text: FULLTIME: Goals. Goals everywhere. Orlando City defeat Columbus Crew SC 5-2. 3 massive points in the eastern conference. #ORLvCLB

timelineItems.name: Jason Paepke
timelineItems.text: Aurelien Colin gets one for each team in the #ORLvCLB game. Nice balanced scoring

timelineItems.name: The Purple Mane
timelineItems.text: Truly cannot believe what I just saw. A total masterclass of a performance in dire circumstances against a great team. #ORLvCLB

timelineItems.name: Alex Stec
timelineItems.text: Stay positive, people. It's one game. #CrewSC will bounce back. We gotta stick together. 💛 #ForColumbus

timelineItems.name: Major League Soccer
timelineItems.text: Larin ties MLS record for goals by a rookie in @OrlandoCitySC's 5-2 win. HIGHLIGHTS: http://t.co/oVDJdKQizh #ORLvCLB http://t.co/vvFfA9ofax

timelineItems.desc: Orlando City SC and Columbus Crew SC meet for a third time this season in a vital match for both clubs' ambitions when they face off Saturday evening at the Citrus Bowl.
timelineItems.title: HIGHLIGHTS: Orlando City SC vs Columbus Crew SC | August 1, 2015

timelineItems.name: Patrick Murphy
timelineItems.text: Really awful defending from #CrewSC. Barson out of position on Ashe, Parkhurst couldn't recover to get a touch on the ball before Larin did.

timelineItems.name: John Bava III
timelineItems.text: 3 times a charm for Cyle Larin as he clinically finishes his 3rd chance of the night to tie it up. The rookie now in double digits. #ORLvCLB

timelineItems.desc: Attempt saved. Kei Kamara (Columbus Crew SC) header from the center of the box is saved in the top center of the goal.
timelineItems.title: SAVE: Tally Hall denies a close range Kei Kamara header

timelineItems.name: Columbus Crew SC
timelineItems.text: 18’: Orlando City goal by Cyle Larin. Corey Ashe hits it off the bounce from the wing and Larin finishes. #CrewSC. #ORLvCLB 1-1

timelineItems.name: City Soccer Talk
timelineItems.text: Larin needs just one more goal to tie the #MLS rookie scoring record. #ORLvCLB

timelineItems.name: Gavin Ewbank
timelineItems.text: BIG save from Tally Hall! Denied Kamaria of his 16th goal of the season, just gets his arm on the ball. #ORLvCLB

timelineItems.name: Adam Jardy
timelineItems.text: 22' Finlay cross to Kamara, but this time his header is saved by Hall at the last second. That usually goes in. #CrewSC

timelineItems.name: City Soccer Talk
timelineItems.text: Loving this Boden/Ashe combination on the left. This formation is kind of a free for all but its working so far #ORLvCLB

timelineItems.desc: Attempt missed. Tony Tchani (Columbus Crew SC) right footed shot from the center of the box is too high.
timelineItems.title: SHOT: Tony Tchani denied by a bit of arm and goalpost

timelineItems.name: John Bava III
timelineItems.text: Halfway through the 1st half and man have we been treated to a some great soccer so far. #CrewSC #OCSC #ORLvCLB

timelineItems.name: Columbus Crew SC
timelineItems.text: 28’: Meram strikes one from outside the 18, but it's deflected by OCSC's Collin. #CrewSC #ORLvCLB

timelineItems.desc: Attempt saved. Kei Kamara (Columbus Crew SC) left footed shot from the left side of the box is saved in the center of the goal.
timelineItems.title: SHOT: Kei Kamara sees his shot saved by Tally Hall

timelineItems.name: Orlando Soccer Daily
timelineItems.text: 29' Kamara header goes off the post! Columbus calling for a handball on Turner who was inside the post. #ORLvCLB

timelineItems.name: Gavin Ewbank
timelineItems.text: Well well well, Orlando City got away with a handball there. Tchani's shot on goal hits Tyler Turner's arm and stays out. No call. #ORLvCLB

timelineItems.name: Marios C Sfantos Esq
timelineItems.text: Electric atmosphere, #ORLvCLB exciting back-&-forth game. @OrlandoCitySC fans/team a first-class football experience! http://t.co/3G4TabDDbh

timelineItems.name: WrongSideOfThePond
timelineItems.text: Tchani shouting for a handball on the #OCSC goal line clearance, and he's right to: it defnitely hit Turner's arm. #CrewSC unlucky there.

timelineItems.name: Columbus Crew SC
timelineItems.text: 30’: Kamara with a step-over and strike. Hall makes another save. #CrewSC creating some dangerous offense. #ORLvCLB

timelineItems.name: Emma Mezzanotte
timelineItems.text: Cyle Larin though. So impressive. #Larin4ROY #ThisIsOrlando #ORLvCLB

timelineItems.name: Columbus Crew SC
timelineItems.text: 33’: Hall meets Pipa's floating cross in the box to cut off an anticipatory Kamara. #CrewSC #ORLvCLB

timelineItems.desc: Goal!  Orlando City SC 2, Columbus Crew SC 1. Darwin Ceren (Orlando City SC) right footed shot from the right side of the box to the top right corner.
timelineItems.title: GOAL: Darwin Ceren volleys home his own rebound for the lead

timelineItems.name: Gavin Ewbank
timelineItems.text: It's Darwin Ceren this time, and #OCSC leads 2-1 in the 38th. That's a great goal. #ORLvCLB

timelineItems.name: Christian Bruey
timelineItems.text: Ridiculous goal from @OrlandoCitySC!! @Kaka never gives up and then @CerenDarwin plays pinball off the @ColumbusCrewSC keeper. #ORLvCLB

timelineItems.text: Kaká did a nice job to save the ball from going out and waited for Ceren to make a run. 2-1 Lions! #ORLvCLB

timelineItems.text: 38' GOAL CEREN! Darwin receives a great ball from Kaka, takes a shot, then drills home the rebound! 2-1 #ORLvCLB

timelineItems.text: WHAT A STRIKE!!!! GOOAAALLLL!!!!! #ORLvCLB http://t.co/fqPC15CmCE

timelineItems.text: 65' Larin with another shot! The Canadian is feeling super-confident tonight. #ORLvCLB

timelineItems.name: Massive Report
timelineItems.text: #CrewSC defense has nothing tonight. This has been hard to watch.

timelineItems.name: The Mane Land
timelineItems.text: 68' - Ceren's blast for the far post flashes wide. Had Clark diving again. #ORLvCLB

timelineItems.name: Daniel Karell
timelineItems.text: Orlando really has #CrewSC's number the last two games. This is wild.

timelineItems.name: City Soccer Talk
timelineItems.text: Ceren hits a screamer just wide. Lions dangerous on every attack at this point. #ORLvCLB

timelineItems.name: City Soccer Talk
timelineItems.text: Higuain runs unmarked right through the center of the defense. Nightmare for the back line again. #ORLvCLB

timelineItems.name: Orlando City SC
timelineItems.text: 6' GOAL. Columbus Crew. Meram finds Higuain on the tail end of his run. He taps it in to give Columbus the lead. 0-1 #ORLvCLB

timelineItems.name: ESPN 580
timelineItems.text: 5'-Meram with a great through ball, just past the penalty spot, right to Higuain who puts it it easily 0-1 #ORLvCLB

timelineItems.name: Columbus Crew SC
timelineItems.text: 5’: GOOOOAL!!!! @FHiguain_33 from @JustinMeram! #CrewSC takes the early lead! #ORLvCLB 0-1 http://t.co/nIGoLaEHej

timelineItems.name: Reid Shoop
timelineItems.text: Down 2 goals and we’ve subbed out 2nd leading goal scorer and 4th leading goal scorer. #confused #CrewSC

timelineItems.name: Four Four Crew
timelineItems.text: The attacking coming in waves for Orlando City. Seems to be only a matter of time before the fourth finds the net. #ORLvCLB

timelineItems.name: John Bava III
timelineItems.text: Every time Larin comes into the box he does so virtually unmarked...and he's already scored a brace. Not good. #CrewSC

timelineItems.name: Sean Connors
timelineItems.text: Still twenty minutes left in this thing and you've got to think Orlando City's good for at least two more goals. #crewsc

timelineItems.desc: Waylon Francis (Columbus Crew SC) is shown the yellow card for a bad foul.
timelineItems.title: YELLOW CARD: Waylon Francis booked for a shoulder charge

timelineItems.name: City Soccer Talk
timelineItems.text: Ceren and Higuita with a lot more freedom to attack this match. Carrasco lying deep making this possible. #ORLvCLB

timelineItems.name: Columbus Crew SC
timelineItems.text: 73’: Francis & Cedrick both serve crosses into the box from either side, but the Lions secure the ball. #CrewSC #ORLvCLB

timelineItems.name: The Mane Land
timelineItems.text: 74' - Francis booked for throwing out the arm and barring Higuita, who went down hard. #ORLvCLB

timelineItems.name: Adam Jardy
timelineItems.text: Waylon Francis will miss next weekend's game due to yellow card accumulation. #CrewSC

timelineItems.desc: Goal!  Orlando City SC 4, Columbus Crew SC 1. Aurelien Collin (Orlando City SC) header from a difficult angle on the right to the high center of goal.
timelineItems.title: GOAL: Aurelien Collin heads home the dagger

timelineItems.name: The Mane Land
timelineItems.text: 76' - GAH! Two great chances for Orlando. Larin can't get on the first one and Hines forces Clark to concede a corner. #ORLvCLB

timelineItems.name: Josie Becker
timelineItems.text: More like Wailin' Francis, amirite? #ORLvCLB

timelineItems.name: The Mane Land
timelineItems.text: 77' - GOAL! Aurelien Collin heads in Boden's corner kick and it's 4-1! #ORLvCLB

timelineItems.name: Scott Crumbly
timelineItems.text: Aurélien Collin finishes a Luke Boden cross, and the Citrus Bowl has turned into a night club. #ORLvCLB

timelineItems.name: Amanda
timelineItems.text: In the words of the announcer: great googly moogly!!! #VamosOrlando @OrlandoCitySC

timelineItems.name: Jason Saghini
timelineItems.text: ...When an announcer comes into a broadcast with only 4 goals calls and a 5th goal is scored... #GreatGooglyMoogly #ORLvCLB #MLS

timelineItems.name: Armin Tamzarian
timelineItems.text: We needed this so badly. 4-1 Orlando City!!!!! A Collin header gives us our first real comfortable home lead. #ORLvCLB

timelineItems.name: Four Four Crew
timelineItems.text: Well 4-1 and this is the worst performance by #CrewSC in a long time. No one seems interested in playing defense. #ORLvCLB

timelineItems.name: Adam Jardy
timelineItems.text: Kamara and Ashe exchanging pleasantries off the ball. Body contact on both sides. This continues to go south. #ORLvCLB

timelineItems.name: Andrew King
timelineItems.text: #CrewSC are absolutely a mess, defensively. No work rate, no awareness, no organization.

timelineItems.name: City Soccer Talk
timelineItems.text: Ceren smashes one over. Orlando City with more scoring chances this match than almost all of July combined. #ORLvCLB

timelineItems.name: The Mane Land
timelineItems.text: 82' -Ceren blasts an open shot just high in the drive for five. #ORLvCLB

timelineItems.desc: Goal!  Orlando City SC 5, Columbus Crew SC 1. Cristian Higuita (Orlando City SC) header from the center of the box to the bottom right corner
timelineItems.title: GOAL: Cristian Higuita piles it on for Orlando's 5th

timelineItems.name: City Soccer Talk
timelineItems.text: Goal Higuita. That locks up his Man of the Match performance. 5-1 #OCSC #ORLvCLB

timelineItems.name: Orlando Soccer Daily
timelineItems.text: 84' ANOTHER GOAL! Higuita heads it past Clark to give the home team a 5-1 lead! #ORLvCLB

timelineItems.name: Matthew Kirby
timelineItems.text: It's FIVE! Kaka crosses & Higuita heads home! #ORLvCLB

timelineItems.name: Sam Fahmi
timelineItems.text: It’s truly disappointing how the back 4 have totally been no help to the front 6 this entire game. Should have signed more defenders #CrewSC

timelineItems.name: Major League Soccer
timelineItems.text: Five. @OrlandoCitySC rooooolllllling. #ORLvCLB

timelineItems.name: Garret Mohler
timelineItems.text: #CrewSC need to scrap everything and go to a 2-5-3 and honestly need to completely rebuild there defensive roster, this is a disappointment

timelineItems.name: Gavin Ewbank
timelineItems.text: Columbus actually led this game 1-0 at one point, in case you forgot. #ORLvCLB

timelineItems.name: Adam Jardy
timelineItems.text: The last time #CrewSC allowed this many goals was in a 6-2 loss to Seattle August 27, 2011.

timelineItems.name: The Mane Land
timelineItems.text: 88' - Rochez mis-hits a Turner cross for what should have been No. 6. City has dominated offensively tonight. #ORLvCLB

timelineItems.name: Scott Carnevale
timelineItems.text: "It's a purple onslaught, a purple tsunami." This will go down as the best @OrlandoCitySC @MLS performance to this point. #ORLvCLB

timelineItems.name: Gavin Ewbank
timelineItems.text: Orlando City's running a very defensive 4-3-3 tonight, and defense was the last thing happening there on Higuain's goal. #ORLvCLB

timelineItems.name: Adam Jardy
timelineItems.text: Gregg Berhalter made a point this week to mention to me that #CrewSC has not yet lost this year when scoring first. Up 1-0 today.

timelineItems.desc: Own Goal by Aurelien Collin, Orlando City SC.  Orlando City SC 5, Columbus Crew SC 2.
timelineItems.title: OWN GOAL: Aurelien Collin scores a great header into his own net

timelineItems.name: The Mane Land
timelineItems.text: 91' - Own goal by Aurelien Collin. Woof. Was trying to keep it away from Higuain. 5-2. #ORLvCLB

timelineItems.name: Purple Reign
timelineItems.text: GOAL - own goal from Collin after a misdirected header as #ORLvCLB enters the beginning of stoppage time

timelineItems.name: Adam Jardy
timelineItems.text: #CrewSC pulls one back thanks to an own goal. 5-2 lead now for the hosts. Collin headed the ball over his own goalkeeper.

timelineItems.name: Katie Patchett
timelineItems.text: Collin forgot which direction to go. Oopsie. He must think the CLB fans needed encouragement. #ORLvCLB #OCJungle

timelineItems.name: Andrew Marcinko
timelineItems.text: You could say that own goal doesn't matter, but Orlando City may well need goal differential to make the playoffs... #ORLvCLB #MLS
